+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Classified all five visible review threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing code.
+
+- Actionable: `T-214-01`, `T-214-04`, `T-214-05`
+- Duplicate: `T-214-02` of `T-214-01`
+- Obsolete: `T-214-03`
+
+The authoritative classification was written to [artifacts/review/thread_triage.json](/private/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260423T232806Z_z7rdi_pj/20260423T232806Z-v4-multi-corpus-objective-run1/workspace/artifacts/review/thread_triage.json:1).
+
+## Changes Made
+
+- [src/policy/approval_router.py](/private/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260423T232806Z_z7rdi_pj/20260423T232806Z-v4-multi-corpus-objective-run1/workspace/src/policy/approval_router.py:17)
+  Normalizes `approval_state` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)`, so `manual_review` no longer leaks into either live or fallback preview responses.
+- [src/policy/preview.py](/private/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260423T232806Z_z7rdi_pj/20260423T232806Z-v4-multi-corpus-objective-run1/workspace/src/policy/preview.py:7)
+  Reused a single base payload for both preview-enabled and preview-unavailable responses, preserving `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` in the fallback response.
+- [tests/test_preview.py](/private/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260423T232806Z_z7rdi_pj/20260423T232806Z-v4-multi-corpus-objective-run1/workspace/tests/test_preview.py:19)
+  Added fallback assertions for the preserved review fields and a regression test covering `preview_enabled=False` with `manual_review` normalization through the router.
+- [docs/approval_policy.md](/private/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260423T232806Z_z7rdi_pj/20260423T232806Z-v4-multi-corpus-objective-run1/workspace/docs/approval_policy.md:9)
+  Updated the documented fallback JSON example to match the corrected runtime payload.
+
+## Verified Outcome
+
+Direct runtime check:
+
+```python
+build_policy_preview(
+    request_id="req-214",
+    approval_state="manual_review",
+    preview_enabled=False,
+    actor="review-bot",
+)
+```
+
+Returned:
+
+```python
+{
+    "request_id": "req-214",
+    "actor": "review-bot",
+    "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+    "requires_human_review": True,
+    "status": "preview_unavailable",
+}
+```
+
+Focused verification:
+
+```bash
+python -m pytest tests/test_preview.py tests/test_approval_router.py
+```
+
+Result: `5 passed in 0.01s`
